Package de.mslab.ciphers

Provides classes which represent implementations of popular block ciphers.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BlockCipher
    Interface for all symmetric ciphers.
    RoundBasedBlockCipher
    Interface for all symmetric ciphers which employ a round-based encryption or decryption.
    TweakableCipher
    Interface for round-based symmetric ciphers which employ a tweak as an additional parameter for encryption or decryption, such as ThreeFish.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AES
    Abstract base class for the AES, as designed 1998 as Rijndael by Daemen and Rijmen.
    AES128  
    AES192  
    AES256  
    ARIA
    Abstract base class for the ARIA block cipher, the South-Korean equivalent to the AES standardized 2003/2004.
    ARIA128  
    ARIA192  
    ARIA256  
    BKSQ144  
    BKSQ192  
    BKSQ96  
    CipherFactory
    Provides an API to create a cipher from name.
    Groestl256Permutation  
    Groestl512Permutation  
    GroestlPermutation
    Base class of the permutations P and Q, used in the Groestl hash function.
    Khazad
    Implements the KHAZAD block cipher, designed 1998 by Rijmen and Barreto.
    KLEIN64  
    KLEIN80  
    KLEIN96  
    LBlock  
    LED
    Implements the LED block cipher, designed 2011 by Guo, Peyrin and al.
    LED112  
    LED128  
    LED64  
    LED80  
    LED96  
    MCrypton  
    MCrypton128  
    MCrypton64  
    MCrypton96  
    PRESENT
    Implements the PRESENT ultra-lightweight block cipher, designed 2007 by Bogdanov, Knudsen et al.
    PRESENT128  
    PRESENT80  
    PRINCE  
    PRINCECore  
    Serpent  
    SQUARE
    Implements the SQUARE block cipher, designed 1998 by Rijmen and Daemen.
    ThreeFish
    Implements the ThreeFish block cipher, which serves as the block cipher used in Skein, and was designed 2009 by Ferguson, Lucks, Schneier et al.
    ThreeFish1024  
    ThreeFish256  
    ThreeFish512  
    WhirlpoolCipher
    Implements the compression function of the hash function WHIRLPOOL, which was designed 2000 by Barreto and Rijmen.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CipherFactory.CipherName
    List of ciphers which can be specified by the user calling the resulting jar of the BicliqueFinderApplication with the console.
